article.headline: New Mexico 86, North Carolina A&T 78
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) -- Chad Toppert had career highs with 20 points and six 3-pointers Saturday and New Mexico, with its leading scorer on the bench in the first half, beat North Carolina A&T 86-78. New Mexico (6-2) never could shake the pesky Aggies (3-6). The difference was the outside shooting of Toppert and the drives to the basket for points by Tony Danridge, who added career highs of 17 points and 6 rebounds. Steven Rush led North Carolina A&T with 28 points. Rush had 6 of the Aggies' 9 3-pointers and hit 9 of 17 shots overall.
